            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Gave it a very hard thought, but then I decided to go for it.\nStarting with the infrastructure and compound, the school stands good. A miniature composition of essential schooling elements is available. If rated it can withstand 4 out of 5. Following CBSE pattern is an added benefit. The nursery is yet to be opened as what I came to know a few days back.\nComing to the quintessential point of rating the school 2 stars. A few days back I went to the school to enquire about the admission process and fees structure. I was accompanied by my wife and my kid (for whom I wanted to know the details). Firstly we were told to wait for a few minutes. After a few while a teacher arrived who then asked about us and went ahead with the procedure and details in an inorder and over professional manner. She never offered us (parents) to sit as she was seated. We remained standing while she was sitting and elaborating things to us.\nOn asking about the dress and uniform code the receptionist briefed us to go to 'sadar bazaar' and contact 'Lovely stores' as they have that privilege, but the school doesn't, as acknowledgedl. I don't know the name but the receptionist (I am not sure whether she too was a teacher of that school) was not even courteous to show us the school uniform.\nPathetic, if the teachers don't have the basic etiquettes of hospitality, what will they teach our children. The foundation in their hands is risky.\nIt's your decision that matters.",
